<paragraph id="E97036DD3F70FFE7FF76FE4DFC66FE04" blockId="69.[151,1437,458,1421]" box="[151,902,458,485]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">
Size. Maximum size about 
<quantity id="2E379B383F70FFE7FE28FE4CFDE0FE04" box="[457,512,458,485]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" unit="cm" value="5.0">5 cm</quantity>
total length (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F70FFE7FD75FE4DFC9AFE04" author="Vanhove, M. P. M. &amp; Kovacic, M. &amp; Koutsikos, N. E. &amp; Zogaris, S. &amp; Vardakas, L. E. &amp; Huyse, T. T. &amp; Economou, A. N." box="[660,890,459,485]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" pagination="195 - 204" refId="ref65691" refString="Vanhove, M. P. M., Kovacic, M., Koutsikos, N. E., Zogaris, S., Vardakas, L. E., Huyse, T. T. &amp; Economou, A. N. (2011) First record of a landlocked population of marine Millerigobius macrocephalus (Perciformes: Gobiidae): Observations from a unique spring-fed karstic lake (Lake Vouliagmeni, Greece) and phylogenetic positioning. Zoologischer Anzeiger, 250, 195 - 204. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. jcz. 2011.03.002" type="journal article" year="2011">
Vanhove 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F70FFE7FD1EFE4DFCD0FE04" box="[767,816,459,485]" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">et al</emphasis>
. 2011
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A1D565563F70FFE7FF26FE69FF00FA6C" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" type="description">
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F70FFE7FF26FE69FB52FD78" blockId="69.[151,1437,458,1421]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">
Morphology. D VI + I,9–11; A I,9–10; 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F70FFE7FD6AFE69FD0AFDE9" bold="true" box="[651,746,494,521]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">P 14–16</emphasis>
. Small goby with stocky body, large head and a short steep snout. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F70FFE7FF05FD94FD0DFDCC" bold="true" box="[228,749,530,557]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Anterior nostril tube long, without tentacle</emphasis>
. Caudal peduncle deep, almost as deep as body. Dorsal fins of similar height, the first with a more or less rounded edge. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F70FFE7FCA3FDB0FEF8FD94" bold="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Only the tip of upper pectoral fin rays is free from membrane</emphasis>
. Caudal fin rounded. Body scaled, predorsal area naked (Miller 1986; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F70FFE7FBC2FDDDFAE4FD94" author="Vanhove, M. P. M. &amp; Kovacic, M. &amp; Koutsikos, N. E. &amp; Zogaris, S. &amp; Vardakas, L. E. &amp; Huyse, T. T. &amp; Economou, A. N." box="[1059,1284,603,629]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" pagination="195 - 204" refId="ref65691" refString="Vanhove, M. P. M., Kovacic, M., Koutsikos, N. E., Zogaris, S., Vardakas, L. E., Huyse, T. T. &amp; Economou, A. N. (2011) First record of a landlocked population of marine Millerigobius macrocephalus (Perciformes: Gobiidae): Observations from a unique spring-fed karstic lake (Lake Vouliagmeni, Greece) and phylogenetic positioning. Zoologischer Anzeiger, 250, 195 - 204. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. jcz. 2011.03.002" type="journal article" year="2011">
Vanhove 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F70FFE7FB6AFDDDFB5BFD94" box="[1163,1211,603,629]" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">et al</emphasis>
. 2011
</bibRefCitation>
). Scales more or less visible on body from the reticulate pattern of pigmentation along scale edges (
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F70FFE7FBB0FDF9FB46FD78" box="[1105,1190,639,665]" captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1583,1607]" captionTargetBox="[162,1426,181,1560]" captionTargetId="figure-18@29.[162,1426,181,1560]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 27. Live coloration of Millerigobius macrocephalus. Broad pale crescent-shaped band across anterior nape behind eyes extending onto rear part of eyes. A) Transverse coloration pattern with pale vertical bars, photo by M. Kovačić, Karinsko ždrilo, eastern Adriatic Sea (in aquarium). B) Coloration pattern reduced to pale dorsal saddles while the rest of body lateral side is more or less uniformly colored or mottled brown, photo by J. Renoult, Corsica, France. C) Anterior nostril without tentacle, photo by J. Renoult, Argelès-sur-Mer, Southern France." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601653" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601653/files/figure.png" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F70FFE7FF26FD25FD00FBC4" blockId="69.[151,1437,458,1421]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">
Live coloration. Body greenish, brownish or dark brown with 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F70FFE7FC41FD24FEB3FD01" bold="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">6–11 narrow, usually indistinct, pale bars across the sides</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F70FFE7FE85FD41FE24FD00" box="[356,452,711,737]" captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1583,1607]" captionTargetBox="[162,1426,181,1560]" captionTargetId="figure-18@29.[162,1426,181,1560]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 27. Live coloration of Millerigobius macrocephalus. Broad pale crescent-shaped band across anterior nape behind eyes extending onto rear part of eyes. A) Transverse coloration pattern with pale vertical bars, photo by M. Kovačić, Karinsko ždrilo, eastern Adriatic Sea (in aquarium). B) Coloration pattern reduced to pale dorsal saddles while the rest of body lateral side is more or less uniformly colored or mottled brown, photo by J. Renoult, Corsica, France. C) Anterior nostril without tentacle, photo by J. Renoult, Argelès-sur-Mer, Southern France." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601653" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601653/files/figure.png" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Fig. 27a</figureCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F70FFE7FE3DFD41FD27FD00" author="Vanhove, M. P. M. &amp; Kovacic, M. &amp; Koutsikos, N. E. &amp; Zogaris, S. &amp; Vardakas, L. E. &amp; Huyse, T. T. &amp; Economou, A. N." box="[476,711,711,737]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" pagination="195 - 204" refId="ref65691" refString="Vanhove, M. P. M., Kovacic, M., Koutsikos, N. E., Zogaris, S., Vardakas, L. E., Huyse, T. T. &amp; Economou, A. N. (2011) First record of a landlocked population of marine Millerigobius macrocephalus (Perciformes: Gobiidae): Observations from a unique spring-fed karstic lake (Lake Vouliagmeni, Greece) and phylogenetic positioning. Zoologischer Anzeiger, 250, 195 - 204. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. jcz. 2011.03.002" type="journal article" year="2011">
Vanhove 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F70FFE7FDABFD41FD9DFD00" box="[586,637,711,737]" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">et al</emphasis>
. 2011
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F70FFE7FD34FD41FC8EFD00" author="Patzner, R. A." box="[725,878,711,737]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" refId="ref62855" refString="Patzner, R. A. (2021) Gobiidae. Available from: http: // www. patzner. sbg. ac. at / Gobiidae / GobiidaeSpecies. htm (accessed 1 October 2021)" type="url" year="2021">Patzner 2021</bibRefCitation>
). In unstressed animals in the wild, side of body often more or less uniformly colored or mottled brown (
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F70FFE7FCE4FD6DFC86FCE7" box="[773,870,747,774]" captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1583,1607]" captionTargetBox="[162,1426,181,1560]" captionTargetId="figure-18@29.[162,1426,181,1560]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 27. Live coloration of Millerigobius macrocephalus. Broad pale crescent-shaped band across anterior nape behind eyes extending onto rear part of eyes. A) Transverse coloration pattern with pale vertical bars, photo by M. Kovačić, Karinsko ždrilo, eastern Adriatic Sea (in aquarium). B) Coloration pattern reduced to pale dorsal saddles while the rest of body lateral side is more or less uniformly colored or mottled brown, photo by J. Renoult, Corsica, France. C) Anterior nostril without tentacle, photo by J. Renoult, Argelès-sur-Mer, Southern France." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601653" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601653/files/figure.png" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Fig. 27b</figureCitation>
). When pale markings are visible on the back, they most often coalesce into a 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F70FFE7FE5EFC88FC73FCC8" bold="true" box="[447,915,782,809]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">highly irregular mediodorsal pale band</emphasis>
(most dark markings on the body not reaching to base of dorsal fins). 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F70FFE7FE7BFCB5FA7CFCAC" bold="true" box="[410,1436,818,845]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Many small pale dots irregularly arranged, especially on snout, preopercle and cheek.</emphasis>
When present, 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F70FFE7FEA3FCD1FD56FC90" bold="true" box="[322,694,855,881]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">the pale crescent band on head</emphasis>
(broad whitish transverse band across anterior nape extending on the sides down to pectoral-fin bases) 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F70FFE7FDA0FCFDFC38FC74" bold="true" box="[577,984,890,917]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">extends onto the rear part of eyes</emphasis>
; it is most often ill-defined (consists of overlapping whitish spots). Often a distinctive and well-defined 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F70FFE7FC97FC18FD93FBE1" bold="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">longitudinal median narrow line on nape and predorsal area, usually formed by a dark dash followed by a white dash, another dark dash, and then a pale line reaching to origin of first dorsal fin</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F70FFE7FD63FC61FD03FBE0" box="[642,739,999,1025]" captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1583,1607]" captionTargetBox="[162,1426,181,1560]" captionTargetId="figure-18@29.[162,1426,181,1560]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 27. Live coloration of Millerigobius macrocephalus. Broad pale crescent-shaped band across anterior nape behind eyes extending onto rear part of eyes. A) Transverse coloration pattern with pale vertical bars, photo by M. Kovačić, Karinsko ždrilo, eastern Adriatic Sea (in aquarium). B) Coloration pattern reduced to pale dorsal saddles while the rest of body lateral side is more or less uniformly colored or mottled brown, photo by J. Renoult, Corsica, France. C) Anterior nostril without tentacle, photo by J. Renoult, Argelès-sur-Mer, Southern France." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601653" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601653/files/figure.png" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Fig. 27c</figureCitation>
). First dorsal fin more or less dark, sometimes reddish, with a whitish horizontal band and often a pale distal edge.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F70FFE7FF26FBA9FD0EFBA8" blockId="69.[151,1437,458,1421]" box="[199,750,1071,1097]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">
Similar species. 
<taxonomicName id="2ECF4D5E3F70FFE7FE9EFBA9FDFDFBA8" authorityName="Benthic" baseAuthorityName="Risso" baseAuthorityYear="1827" box="[383,541,1071,1097]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Zebrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="zebrus">
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F70FFE7FE9EFBA9FDFDFBA8" box="[383,541,1071,1097]" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Zebrus zebrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2ECF4D5E3F70FFE7FDCAFBA9FD07FBA8" authorityName="Kovacic, Sanda &amp; Vukic" authorityYear="2021" box="[555,743,1071,1097]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Zebrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pallaoroi">
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F70FFE7FDCAFBA9FD07FBA8" box="[555,743,1071,1097]" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Zebrus pallaoroi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F70FFE7FF26FBD5FB12FB70" blockId="69.[151,1437,458,1421]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">
Habitat. Infralittoral species, known from 
<quantity id="2E379B383F70FFE7FD40FBD4FD16FB8C" box="[673,758,1106,1133]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="0.1" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" unit="m" value="13.0" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="1.0">1–25 m</quantity>
depth on stones and pebbles near soft bottoms (summarized by 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F70FFE7FF5BFBF1FEB1FB70" author="Patzner, R. A." box="[186,337,1143,1169]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" refId="ref62855" refString="Patzner, R. A. (2021) Gobiidae. Available from: http: // www. patzner. sbg. ac. at / Gobiidae / GobiidaeSpecies. htm (accessed 1 October 2021)" type="url" year="2021">Patzner 2021</bibRefCitation>
). Also recorded in transition waters, hypersaline or brackish (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F70FFE7FBE1FBF1FB06FB70" author="Vanhove, M. P. M. &amp; Kovacic, M. &amp; Koutsikos, N. E. &amp; Zogaris, S. &amp; Vardakas, L. E. &amp; Huyse, T. T. &amp; Economou, A. N." box="[1024,1254,1143,1169]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" pagination="195 - 204" refId="ref65691" refString="Vanhove, M. P. M., Kovacic, M., Koutsikos, N. E., Zogaris, S., Vardakas, L. E., Huyse, T. T. &amp; Economou, A. N. (2011) First record of a landlocked population of marine Millerigobius macrocephalus (Perciformes: Gobiidae): Observations from a unique spring-fed karstic lake (Lake Vouliagmeni, Greece) and phylogenetic positioning. Zoologischer Anzeiger, 250, 195 - 204. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. jcz. 2011.03.002" type="journal article" year="2011">
Vanhove 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F70FFE7FB8AFBF1FB7CFB70" box="[1131,1180,1143,1169]" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">et al</emphasis>
. 2011
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F70FFE7FF26FB1DFF00FA6C" blockId="69.[151,1437,458,1421]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">
Geographic distribution. Mediterranean and Black Sea. In the Mediterranean Sea, there are records from Ibiza (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F70FFE7FF7EFB39FDD4FB38" author="Ramos-Espla, A. A. &amp; Perez-Ruzafa, A." box="[159,564,1215,1241]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" pagination="31 - 35" refId="ref63361" refString="Ramos-Espla, A. A. &amp; Perez-Ruzafa, A. (1987) Presencia de Millerigobius macrocephalus (Kolombatovic, 1891) (Teleostei: Gobiidae) en el Mediterraneo occidental con notas sobre su biologia. Anales de Biologia, 11, 31 - 35." type="journal article" year="1987">Ramos-Espla &amp; Perez-Ruzafa 1987</bibRefCitation>
), Cerbère, Gulf of Lion (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F70FFE7FCABFB39FBF9FB38" author="Duhau, M. &amp; Pillon, R. &amp; Louisy, P." box="[842,1049,1215,1241]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" refId="ref53575" refString="Duhau, M., Pillon, R. &amp; Louisy, P. (2021) Signalisation de / Record of Millerigobius macrocephalus, 13 December 2021 (obs. 24 June 2021, photo  5924). Fish Watch Forum, Louisy, P. &amp; Francour, P. (Ed.). Available from: https: // www. fish-watch. org (accessed 15 December 2021)" type="url" year="2021">
Duhau 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F70FFE7FC7FFB39FC2FFB38" box="[926,975,1215,1241]" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">et al</emphasis>
. 2021
</bibRefCitation>
), southern 
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F70FFE7FB75FB39FB0AFB38" box="[1172,1258,1215,1241]" name="France" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Corsica</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F70FFE7FB19FB39FEA1FB1C" author="Bouchereau, J. L. &amp; Tomasini, J. A." pageId="69" pageNumber="70" pagination="106 - 110" refId="ref52448" refString="Bouchereau, J. L. &amp; Tomasini, J. A. (1989) Note sur la presence de Chromogobius zebratus (Kolombatovic, 1891) et de Millerigobius macrocephalus (Kolombatovic, 1891) (Teleostei; Percomorphi; Gobioidei; Gobiidae) sur les cotes de Corse, France. Bulletin de la Societe zoologique de France Societe zoologique de France, 114, 106 - 110." type="journal article" year="1989">Bouchereau &amp; Tomasini 1989</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F70FFE7FEADFB65FDD4FB1F" author="Renoult, J. P. &amp; Pillon, R. &amp; Louisy, P." box="[332,564,1251,1278]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" refId="ref63645" refString="Renoult, J. P., Pillon, R. &amp; Louisy, P. (2021 b) Signalisation de / Record of Millerigobius macrocephalus, 13 December 2021 (obs. 05 July 2020, photo  5910). Fish Watch Forum, Louisy, P. &amp; Francour, P. (Ed.). Available from: https: // www. fish-watch. org (accessed 13 December 2021)" type="url" year="2021">
Renoult 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F70FFE7FE4AFB65FE3CFB1C" box="[427,476,1251,1277]" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">et al</emphasis>
. 2021b
</bibRefCitation>
), Sicily (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F70FFE7FD76FB65FC66FB1F" author="Giacobbe, S. &amp; Spinelli, A. &amp; De Matteo, S. &amp; Kovacic, M." box="[663,902,1251,1278]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" pagination="49 - 52" refId="ref54950" refString="Giacobbe, S., Spinelli, A., De Matteo, S. &amp; Kovacic, M. (2016) First record of the large-headed goby, Millerigobius macrocephalus (Actinopterygii: Perciformes: Gobiidae), from Italy. Acta Ichthyologica et Piscatoria, 46, 49 - 52. https: // doi. org / 10.3750 / AIP 2016.46.1.07" type="journal article" year="2016">
Giacobbe 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F70FFE7FCEAFB65FCDCFB1C" box="[779,828,1251,1277]" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F70FFE7FC78FB65FC3AFB1C" box="[921,986,1251,1277]" name="Malta" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Malta</collectingCountry>
(Kovačić 
