<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F70FFE7FEEDFAC9FE8EFA88" box="[268,366,1359,1385]" name="Lebanon" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Lebanon</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F70FFE7FE9DFAC9FDE7FA88" author="Miller, P. J." box="[380,519,1359,1385]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" pagination="339 - 362" refId="ref61444" refString="Miller, P. J. (1977) Gobies from Rhodes and systematic features of Zebrus zebrus (Teleostei: Gobiidae). Zoologicla Journal of Linnean Soc iety, 60, 339 - 362. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1977. tb 00839. x" type="journal article" year="1977">Miller 1977</bibRefCitation>
). Large-headed goby was also found in Crimea, in the Black Sea (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F70FFE7FB0BFAC9FF34FA6C" author="Boltachev, A. R. &amp; Karpova, E. P. &amp; Machkevskiy, V. K." pageId="69" pageNumber="70" pagination="32" refId="ref52396" refString="Boltachev, A. R., Karpova, E. P. &amp; Machkevskiy, V. K. (2010) The naturalization of Miller's goby Millerigobius macrocephalus (Perciformes, Gobiidae) in the Sevastopol Bay of the Black Sea. Morskoj ekologiceskij zurnal, 9, 32." type="journal article" year="2010">
Boltachev 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F70FFE7FA85FAC9FA75FA88" box="[1380,1429,1359,1385]" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">et al</emphasis>
. 2010
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
